<br>
If the question is directed toward the legality, I would agree let the courts decide after which the community can make its own judgement.  If the question addresses the moral and ethical behavior,  that's not an issue the court will address and belongs with the community.<br>
<br>
One should wait for all the facts,  but I'll give a lot more weight to what I see with my own eyes than I will to what I'm *told* to believe.   On a side note cameras are not so decieving as to not be allowed as evidence and are frequently the tool of police investigations.<br>
